reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars LOVE MY NEW DESK
reviews.reviewText: I'm really enjoying my new desk. Lots of space to work very comfortably. I'm using it in my home office but it will also be perfect for a work space. Functional and also very stylish.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It can be reversed, kind of
reviews.reviewText: Overall I am pretty happy with the desk.The final result, for me, is a overall very sharp-looking, spacious, useful, modern-looking desk. A tiny portion of the intended functionality is compromised because the space I had for it mandated reversing the design, which it is not designed to do. The build quality is low, but this is only really obvious while you are assembling it; the final product looks as nice as much, much more expensive desks. For the price I think this is easily worth it, but keep in mind you are sacrificing ease of assembly for the low cost and elegant look.The desk is not meant to be reversible, and if you do want to reverse it you have to make a few sacrifices. For one, the lower shelving unit's backplate is designed to friction-fit into pre-cut guide trenches that exist only on one side; I simply neglected to attach the backplate, but you might be able to screw it onto the other side. The same is true for the shelving unit's cabinet door. Reversing the actual desk part is fairly simple; you attach the two long bars to the top desk pieces as usual, but put the feet and the shelf attachments on at the opposite ends of the instructions.Of note, it does not ship with the tools you need to assemble it; you will need a basic phillips-head screwdriver, ideally with a replaceable bit and a handful of bit sizes. It does arrive, strangely, with a flathead screwdriver, but does not have any flathead screws. It also arrived with a single hex wrench that was properly sized for the hex screws it uses.It is very cheap for what it is. That helps a lot with satisfaction; if this were a $3k desk it would absolutely not be worth it. The cheapness also shows in the desk's build quality. The holes drilled into the bottom of the attached shelving unit, for example, were not placed in the correct locations and did not fit the legs; I had to make my own holes for them to attach properly. Tolerances on a lot of the other pieces were extremely varied; pilot holes were generally more aspirational than useful. The dark gray finish shows fingerprints like crazy, but fingerprints aren't visible on the wood-finished parts at all.The shelving unit has a surprising amount of capacity. Some of it relatively inaccessible, though, because it is placed directly beneath the far corner of the desk and hard to reach. As long as you keep stuff you only rarely need in that portion, though, it's a lot of quite useful space.The support bars below the main desk are mildly annoying, my legs do bump into/brush them frequently. If you are able to sit with your seat a fair bit below the desk, though, this is less likely to be an issue.Overall, 8/10 for me. Pretty pleased with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I'll start with the cons. Some of the items were mislabeled, the instructions are very "feel your way through it", and a piece was damaged. With that being said, I love this desk. The instructions aren't the clearest but are manageable. When putting it together, a lot of the pieces are universal so you can flip it around and still get to the end piece. The only time I put something together that was wrong is before you put the table top on (attached the picture of how it should be so you don't do it wrong like I did, stress about it not fitting, and loose 30-45 mins of your time). The damaged piece (pictured) was just bent and fortunately did not interfere with the process at all. I only planned to reach out to the manufacturer if it stopped me from putting the desk together but it all worked out.One of the things I love the most is desk and the cabinet are 2 separate pieces. If you move or something along those lines, you can essentially lift the table off the cabinet portion and transport them individually. Extremely impressed with this desk and happy with the purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice desk with a different look to it
reviews.reviewText: I really like this desk, and how much space I have on it. I paired it with a monitor riser that resembles the desk, and I now have even more space. It is a little difficult to move. If you need to reposition, you really need furniture movers under each leg, because if you try to lift it, the top will come unattached from the side piece.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars DO NOT BUY
reviews.reviewText: I am furious after purchasing this product. The quality of the product is very poor and flimsy. The desk came with scratches, rust, misplaced screwholes and the styrofoam that was meant to protect the item was very poor standard and falling apart once package was opened. After complaining to company it is clear they are an Amazon reseller with no responsibility over item and no interest in providing customer service. I have asked to have item returned and they kept trying to ask to exchange different pieces of desk or “$30” in compensation with no change to item as if it would resolve issue. They have become non-responsive now. I deeply regret purchasing this product, and would urge anyone else considering purchasing a product with this company to avoid at all costs. The images and price point are appealing, but it is a false representation of the company and the product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good looking desk. The material matches the price...If shipped without damage.
reviews.reviewText: I paid $323 plus tax—a good price for a 79-inch L-shaped desk with a modern look. The single door is slow-hinged, so it closes nicely, and never slams closed. The cable ports and air vents are a nice touch. It is very much like an IKEA desk. It will take some time to put together.You might want to expect some damage. Like some other customers, several of my panels had shipping damage on the corners; see photos. Most of my damaged corners are conveniently located in the back of a cubby area or the shelf... You may not be so lucky. I don't know how the seller would handle a damage claim...I would expect them to make it right...I may find out shortly...

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality and very functional.
reviews.reviewText: I've been using this desk for several months now and love it. It was a challenge to assemble because it is a complex piece. However, with two people and given the good hole alignments, the excellent instructions, and the high quality materials (well packaged and all parts present), it's very doable. We actually had disassemble it after a few months and reassemble it at another location - no problem. Well worth the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars nice looking desk but doesn’t ship well
reviews.reviewText: i love the look and size of this desk but it definitely doesn’t travel well. came with several damaged pieces. putting it together is tough when you do it by yourself, definitely recommend having a second set of hands to help.
